title: Grateful Dead Live at Henry J. Kaiser Convention Center on 1985-09-10
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw-> Peggy-O, Little Red Rooster, Stagger Lee, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues-> Ramble On Rose, Cassidy-> Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Good Time Blues*-> Drums-> China Doll-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Around & Around-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Day Job

*without Jerry

reviews.review_text:
Fun times.....Liquid light shows This was a great little tour threw the southwest and back to our home the Kaisers.
before the stadiums and big stage along with visual stage these 3 nights were the Liquid light shows. With all the old photos of the band members and cartoons running in the background along with the trippy liquid light display. 
Quality of this one is very good 4 stars to me 5 because there other show with the 5 star sound. Still that should take nothing away from this night and the next 2 also. Fun trippy times back then. 
 Oh how lucky we were to have been apart of such a great scene back then and to come out on the other side sober  I sure am glad to have done all that I did and not only survive but to have this great site to enjoy my favorite band and shows. Huge HUGE thanks to all that make this happen.
